<recipe>
    <name>Persian Chicken With Rice (Zereshk Polo ba Morgh)</name>
    <indexCharacter>P</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>
1. NOTE: IF FIXING ON A WEEKNIGHT, FIX THE RICE ONE NIGHT BEFORE!
2. Start preparing Persian Rice first, because of soaking time required
3. Chop the onion
4. Pour enough oil into a large, flat pan to saut√© the onion pieces
5. Remove the skin from the chicken pieces
6. Wash the chicken pieces
7. Place the chicken pieces on top of the onion pieces, bone sides down
8. Cover the pan and cook for about five minutes
9. Sprinkle a little salt on the chicken
10. Sprinkle the chicken liberally with turmeric, cinnamon and Persian spice mix
11. Turn the chicken pieces over
12. Sprinkle the salt and spices on the bottom of the chicken
13. Put the lid on the pan and cook for 30 minutes
14. Begin preparing the candied barberries
15. After 30 minutes, turn the chicken pieces over and cook for another 15 minutes
16. Drizzle some butter on the chicken pieces, then put the lid back on the pan
17. Plate rice (she spread across the whole plate)
18. Plate candied barberries as a small stripe across the middle of the plate
19. Plate pistachios on one side of the barberry and chicken on the other
20. Spread some of the cooking juices from the chicken on top of the chicken</instructions>
